parameters.name: index group_index business_type port_id
parameters.description: ID of index group_index business_type port_id

card-position.description: Card position. The position is expressed in the format of slotID/cardID. For example, 1/0. Here 1/0 is an example. The value may vary with devices.

padding-enable.description: Enable/disable automatic overhead frame padding. You are advised to use the leaf '/flexe:flexe/flexe:groups/flexe:group/flexe:padding'.

physical-ports.description: List of physical port information in group.

port-position.description: Physical port location. The position is expressed in the format of slotID/cardID/portID. For example, 1/0/1. Here 1/0/1 is an example. The value may vary with devices.

position.description: Port position. The position is expressed in the format of slotID/cardID/portID. For example, 1/0/1. Here 1/0/1 is an example. The value may vary with devices.

number.description: Number of a FlexE physical port. The phynumber of a 100G port is an integer ranging from 1 to 254. The phynumber of a 50G port is an integer ranging from 1 to 126. The phynumber of a 400G port is an integer ranging from 1 to 62. The phynumber of a 10G port is an integer ranging from 1 to 14.

number-to-receive.description: Number received by a FlexE physical port.

used-timeslot.description: Big timeslots that have been used up.

physical-mode.description: Bottom layer working mode of a FlexE physical port.

card-position.description: Indicates the subcard where the FlexE clients created based on the FlexE physical interface reside.

flexe-relations.description: List of timeslot information of FlexE port.

flexe-relation.description: Statistics of timeslot information of a FlexE port.

binding-timeslot.description: Timeslot information bound to a FlexE port.

group-index.description: FlexE group index configured for a client.

business-type.description: Type of services carried on a client.

min-avail-bandwidth.description: Percentage of the minimum available bandwidth of a FlexE client against the configured bandwidth.

port-name.description: Interface name of a FlexE client.

physical-port-name.description: FlexE physical port name. The name is expressed in the format of slotID/cardID/portID. For example, 1/0/1. Here 1/0/1 is an example. The value may vary with devices.

binding-timeslot.description: Binding big time slot or sub time slot.

timeslot.description: Set timeslot. The value is one or more numbers separated by commas (,) or hyphens (-). If the values are separated by '-', they must be in ascending order. For example, correct range values are (0-1) and incorrect range values are (1-0).

sub-timeslot.description: Set sub-timeslot. The value is one or more numbers separated by commas (,) or hyphens (-). If the values are separated by '-', they must be in ascending order. For example, correct range values are (0-1) and incorrect range values are (1-0).

card-position.description: Card position. The position is expressed in the format of slotID/cardID. For example, 1/0. Here 1/0 is an example. The value may vary with devices.
